main event: A bright orange object was observed passing over Feasterville, Pennsylvania at a high rate of speed on July 8, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 30 seconds and appeared to be saucer-shaped, about the size of a basketball at arm's length.
The object proceeded in a southwest direction and disappeared from sight.
No specific sounds were heard from the object.
No other witnesses could be located at the time of the incident.
The witness, Richard Greene, was an Air Force veteran who seemed reliable with no signs of alcoholism or emotional disturbance.
witnesses: Richard Greene, an Air Force veteran
